National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with Japanese National Security Advisor Shotaro Yachi at the White House. They agreed to have regular communication between the two National Security Councils and discussed updating their defense partnership. They also discussed their collaborative efforts to achieve denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. The National Security Council staff also had consultations with Yachi's delegation, and they look forward to continuing close consultation with the new Japanese National Security Council to strengthen U.S.-Japan relations.